<sect2 id="gimp-file-open-as-link-layer">

  <title>Open as Link Layer…</title>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Image</primary>
    <secondary>Open</secondary>
    <tertiary>As link layer</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Layer</primary>
    <secondary>Stack managing</secondary>
    <tertiary>Open image as link layer</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Open as link layer</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <para>
    The <guimenu>Open as link layer</guimenu> command opens the
    <link linkend="gimp-open-dialog">Open Image</link> dialog. The image is added
    as a so-called <link linkend="gimp-layer-type-link-layer">Link Layer</link>
    that can be changed and updated separately.
  </para>
  <sect3>
    <title>Activating the Command</title>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can access this command from the main menu through
          <menuchoice>
            <guimenu>File</guimenu>
            <guimenuitem>Open as Link Layer…</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can also use the keyboard shortcut
          <keycombo>
            <keycap>Shift</keycap>
            <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
            <keycap>O</keycap>
          </keycombo>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
